      • ChessDomain

        public ChessDomain(Chrest model,
                   java.lang.Integer initialFixationThreshold,
                   int fixationPeripheryMaxAttempts,
                   int maxFixationsInSet,
                   int timeTakenToDecideOnGlobalStrategyFixations,
                   int timeTakenToDecideOnSalientManFixations)
        Constructor.
        Parameters:
        model - The Chrest model that is situated in a chess domain.
        initialFixationThreshold - The number of Fixations that can be made by the Chrest model constructing #this before it is no longer considered to be making initial Fixations in a set (see #this#doneInitialFixations(int)). If the value specified for this parameter is null, a value of 4 is used since this is the default value for this parameter as specified in the "Salient-Man" fixation heuristic description in section 8.7.6 of "Perception and Memory in Chess" by de Groot and Gobet. If the value specified for this parameter is not null, it must be greater than 0 otherwise a IllegalArgumentException will be thrown.
        fixationPeripheryMaxAttempts - If a PeripheralItemFixation is attempted, this parameter specified how many attempts will be made to find a suitable Square in the periphery before attempting the PeripheralItemFixation is abandoned (see jchrest.domainSpecifics.fixations.PeripheralItemFixation#PeripheralItemFixation( jchrest.architecture.Chrest, int, int)).
        maxFixationsInSet - When making a set of Fixations, this parameter defines how many can be attempted in total before a new set is initialised (see #this#shouldClearFixations(int).
        timeTakenToDecideOnGlobalStrategyFixations -
        timeTakenToDecideOnSalientManFixations -

      • validMove

        public static boolean validMove(ChessBoard board,
                                Square source,
                                Square destination)
        Parameters:
        board -
        source - Must contain a non-empty ChessObject.
        destination -
        Returns:
        Boolean.TRUE if the destination is empty or could result in a capture, i.e. if either of the following statements are Boolean.TRUE, Boolean.FALSE otherwise:
        1. jchrest.lib.Scene#isSquareEmpty(int, int) returns Boolean.TRUE in context of the board and destination specified.
        2. #this#differentColour(jchrest.lib.Scene, jchrest.lib.Square, jchrest.lib.Square) returns Boolean.TRUE in context of the board, source and destination specified.
        NOTE: this function does not check if the movement of the piece from the source to the destination is valid according to the result of invoking SceneObject.getObjectType() on the ChessObject present on source, i,e. if source contains a queen and desitination can only be reached using a knight movement but destination is empty or contains a ChessObject of a different colour to the queen, this function will return Boolean.TRUE.

      • getPawnMoves

        public static java.lang.Object[] getPawnMoves(ChessBoard board,
                                              Square square)
        Parameters:
        board -
        square - Must contain a black/white pawn ChessObject.
        Returns:
        A two-element Array whose first element is a List of Squares that the pawn can move to and whose second element is the number of Squares considered when calculating where the pawn could be moved to. The function will check if the pawn can:
        • Make a standard move: is the Square that's 1 ahead of the square specified empty?
        • Make an initial move: is the Square that's 2 ahead of the square specified empty?
        • Capture any pieces: are the squares to the immediate diagonal left/right of the square specified occupied by white pieces (note that en-passant captures are ignored)?

      • getKnightMoves

        public static java.lang.Object[] getKnightMoves(ChessBoard board,
                                                Square square)
        Parameters:
        board -
        square - Must contain a knight ChessObject.
        Returns:
        A two-element Array whose first element is a List of Squares that the knight can move to and whose second element is the number of Squares considered when calculating what Squares can be moved to. The function will check if the Squares that the knight can move to are empty or are occupied by pieces of a different colour, i.e. whether it can capture any pieces.

      • getKingMoves

        public static java.lang.Object[] getKingMoves(ChessBoard board,
                                              Square square)
        Parameters:
        board -
        square - Must contain a king ChessObject.
        Returns:
        A two-element Array whose first element is a List of Squares that the king can move to and whose second element is the number of Squares considered when calculating what Squares can be moved to. The function will check if the Squares that the king can move to are empty or are occupied by pieces of a different colour, i.e. whether it can capture any pieces. NOTE: this function does not check if the Square moved to will put the king in check, if it is 1 square from a king of the opposing colour or if a capture may result in the king moving to a Square occupied by a king ChessObject of the opposing colour.

      • normalise

        public ListPattern normalise(ListPattern pattern)
        Description copied from class: DomainSpecifics
        Used to prepare ListPatterns for input to long-term memory by a Chrest model. Implementing this enables Modality.VISUAL ListPatterns to be stripped of ItemSquarePatterns that denote empty Squares in a Scene, for example.
        Specified by:
        normalise in class DomainSpecifics
        Parameters:
        pattern -
        Returns:
        The ListPattern specified after sorting its constituent ItemSquarePatterns into a canonical order of chess pieces, as defined in section 8.7.1, paragraph "C: Comparison with other models." in "Perception and Memory in Chess" by de Groot and Gobet (1996). This order is: P p K k B b N n Q q R r. If the pieces are the same, then order is based on column, and then on row.

      • getNonInitialFixationInSet

        public Fixation getNonInitialFixationInSet(int time)
        Description copied from class: DomainSpecifics
        Used by Chrest.scheduleOrMakeNextFixation(jchrest.domainSpecifics.Scene, boolean, boolean, int).
        Specified by:
        getNonInitialFixationInSet in class DomainSpecifics
        Parameters:
        time -
        Returns:
        A new Fixation whose type is determined by comparing n (the sum of the number of Fixations to make and the number of Fixations attempted at the time specified) to t (the initial Fixation threshold specified as a parameter to #this#TileworldDomain(jchrest.architecture.Chrest, int, int, int)):
        1. If n < t a SalientManFixation is returned.
        2. If n >= t, the Fixations scheduled to be performed and the most recent Fixation attempted by the Chrest model using #this are retrieved in context of the time specified.
          1. If there is no HypothesisDiscriminationFixation scheduled to be performed or the most recently attempted Fixation was a HypothesisDiscriminationFixation whose performance was unsuccessful, a HypothesisDiscriminationFixation is returned.
          2. If there is a HypothesisDiscriminationFixation scheduled to be performed or the most recently attempted Fixation was a HypothesisDiscriminationFixation that was performed successfully, one of the following Fixations are returned with equal probability:
            • AttackDefenseFixation
            • PeripheralSquareFixation
            • Get e (the result of invoking Chrest.isExperienced(int) in context of the Chrest model using #this).
              • If e is Boolean.TRUE, return a GlobalStrategyFixation.
              • If e is Boolean.FALSE, return a PeripheralItemFixation.

      • shouldLearnFromNewFixations

        public boolean shouldLearnFromNewFixations(int time)
        Description copied from class: DomainSpecifics
        Used by Chrest.scheduleOrMakeNextFixation(jchrest.domainSpecifics.Scene, boolean, boolean, int) to determine if any Fixations successfully performed by the Perceiver associated with the Chrest model invoking Chrest.scheduleOrMakeNextFixation(jchrest.domainSpecifics.Scene, boolean, boolean, int) that have not been learned yet, should be. NOTE: Chrest.scheduleOrMakeNextFixation(jchrest.domainSpecifics.Scene, boolean, boolean, int) already checks for a SceneObject or Square being focused on again since the last time Chrest.scheduleOrMakeNextFixation(jchrest.domainSpecifics.Scene, boolean, boolean, int) was invoked.
        Specified by:
        shouldLearnFromNewFixations in class DomainSpecifics
        Parameters:
        time -
        Returns:
        Boolean.TRUE if any of the following statements evaluate to Boolean.TRUE for the Fixation most recently performed by the Perceiver associated with the Chrest model using #this (based upon the time specified). Otherwise, Boolean.FALSE is returned:
        1. Fixation was made on an empty Square.
        2. Fixation was a GlobalStrategyFixation.
        3. Fixation was a PeripheralItemFixation.
        4. Fixation was performed on a Square that has been fixated on before in this set of Fixations.
        Boolean.FALSE is also returned if the Perceiver associated with the Chrest model was not created at the time specified or no Fixations have been added to the Perceiver at the time specified.
